1
00:00:18,394 --> 00:00:19,603
Yeah, come in!

2
00:00:21,605 --> 00:00:22,857
Mr. Lennington.

3
00:00:23,232 --> 00:00:26,193
Srikant Tiwari of NIA is on the line
for you from India.

4
00:00:27,820 --> 00:00:30,156
-Yeah, put him through.
-Okay, thank you.

5
00:00:35,035 --> 00:00:36,954
Getting a patch from Islamabad.

6
00:00:37,246 --> 00:00:39,707
Sir, connecting you to
Bruce Lennington in Islamabad.

7
00:00:41,834 --> 00:00:44,044
-Hi, Bruce.
-Hey, Srikant.

8
00:00:44,128 --> 00:00:45,588
Been a while!
How have you been?

9
00:00:45,629 --> 00:00:47,673
I've been fine. How are you?

10
00:00:47,757 --> 00:00:50,134
All good. What's happening?
What's up?

11
00:00:50,342 --> 00:00:52,136
Okay, Bruce.
I have someone...

12
00:00:52,303 --> 00:00:54,513
you've been desperately
looking for.

13
00:00:54,889 --> 00:00:57,933
-Go on. I'm all ears.
 -Faizan Ahmed.

14
00:00:59,226 --> 00:01:00,811
-Tell me.
-I have his satellite number

15
00:01:00,895 --> 00:01:02,521
and the location where he's hiding.

16
00:01:02,605 --> 00:01:04,064
You're sure it's Faizan?

17
00:01:04,482 --> 00:01:05,816
Absolutely.

18
00:01:06,859 --> 00:01:07,860
Where is he now?

19
00:01:07,943 --> 00:01:11,280
Somewhere in Zhob province, 
 in Balochistan.

20
00:01:11,822 --> 00:01:14,200
-You have his exact location?
-Not yet.

21
00:01:14,658 --> 00:01:15,951
But we'll get it.

22
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:18,037
But I need a favor from you in return.

23
00:01:18,162 --> 00:01:19,413
What favor?

24
00:01:19,663 --> 00:01:21,415
I want to have a chat
with him in person.

25
00:01:22,416 --> 00:01:23,626
That...

26
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:25,586
I don't know how we're
going to achieve that.

27
00:01:25,669 --> 00:01:26,754
I mean, assuming we do nab him

28
00:01:26,837 --> 00:01:28,714
I'm not going to be able
to bring him to India.

29
00:01:30,132 --> 00:01:31,467
Well...

30
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:34,845
If the mountain doesn't
come to Muḥammad...

31
00:01:37,389 --> 00:01:39,308
Alright. What's the plan?

32
00:01:39,683 --> 00:01:41,143
Two words.

33
00:01:41,227 --> 00:01:43,229
Dzhokhar Dudayev.

34
00:01:43,938 --> 00:01:45,356
And you think that will work?

35
00:01:45,481 --> 00:01:48,150
Dzhokhar Dudayev was
a Chechen rebel.

36
00:01:48,234 --> 00:01:50,402
The KGB used a similar plan to get him.

37
00:01:50,528 --> 00:01:52,196
You think this plan will work?

38
00:01:52,279 --> 00:01:53,823
With a bit of luck.

39
00:01:53,906 --> 00:01:55,866
Just a second.
Yeah, Zoya?

40
00:01:55,991 --> 00:01:57,660
Sir, the tech team has
processed the voice sample

41
00:01:57,743 --> 00:01:59,370
and they've sent us an
audio fingerprint back.

42
00:01:59,495 --> 00:02:00,329
What do you think?

43
00:02:00,412 --> 00:02:02,248
Sir, it might work, 
 but there's a problem.

44
00:02:02,331 --> 00:02:03,415
The sample is too short.

45
00:02:03,499 --> 00:02:05,251
A longer sample would've worked better.

46
00:02:05,376 --> 00:02:07,336
This is it, Zoya.
We don't have time.

47
00:02:07,419 --> 00:02:08,420
-Send it!
-Okay, sir.

48
00:02:08,504 --> 00:02:10,714
Sending it to you right away.
And, sir...

49
00:02:11,382 --> 00:02:13,467
-Good luck.
-Thank you, Zoya.

50
00:02:17,263 --> 00:02:18,806
Okay, these are the six safe houses

51
00:02:18,889 --> 00:02:20,266
around the coordinates we received.

52
00:02:20,349 --> 00:02:21,725
He could be hiding in any one of these.

53
00:02:21,809 --> 00:02:23,686
Tracking all these
houses as we speak.

54
00:02:23,769 --> 00:02:26,397
Beaming visuals onto the screens. 
 We've got tactical units

55
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,024
in striking distance
at all these locations. You copy?

56
00:02:29,108 --> 00:02:30,901
Are you sure that these are
the only possible places

57
00:02:30,985 --> 00:02:32,570
-where he could be?
 -I hope so.

58
00:02:32,653 --> 00:02:34,238
These are the only locations we know

59
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:36,615
-that General Ansari uses.
-Okay.

60
00:02:36,699 --> 00:02:37,867
How are things going on 
 at your end?

61
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:39,743
Well, using the voice sample

62
00:02:39,827 --> 00:02:42,204
from the conversation
of Sajid with Faizan

63
00:02:42,288 --> 00:02:44,707
we've managed to put
together his voice profile.

64
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:46,876
I think we can manage with that.

65
00:02:46,959 --> 00:02:48,127
Play it.

66
00:02:49,086 --> 00:02:50,546
As-salaam alaikum, brother.

67
00:02:50,629 --> 00:02:51,964
Hello, I can't hear you--

68
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:54,383
No. It's too clear.
Add some more noise.

69
00:02:56,552 --> 00:02:58,053
As-salaam alaikum, brother.

70
00:02:58,137 --> 00:02:59,847
Hello, I can't hear you, brother.

71
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:00,764
The network's bad.

72
00:03:00,848 --> 00:03:02,558
Very good. Play this one.

73
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:04,894
-Bruce, we're ready.
-Copy.

74
00:03:05,477 --> 00:03:06,562
Connecting, sir.

75
00:03:08,606 --> 00:03:10,399
All teams on standby
for target location.

76
00:03:10,482 --> 00:03:12,568
TU1 is active and ready to launch.

77
00:03:20,117 --> 00:03:21,327
Try again.

78
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:23,495
-Negative, sir.
-Connecting again, sir.

79
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:28,417
Hello?

80
00:03:29,501 --> 00:03:31,253
As-salaam alaikum, brother.

81
00:03:31,921 --> 00:03:34,214
Wa alaykumu as-salam, Sajid.
All well?

82
00:03:34,298 --> 00:03:35,424
How did you find this number?

83
00:03:35,507 --> 00:03:37,134
Hello, I can't hear you, brother.

84
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:39,219
-Play it.
-Hello!

85
00:03:39,386 --> 00:03:41,096
Hello, I can't hear you, brother.

86
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:42,431
Wait, let me go to the terrace.

87
00:03:42,514 --> 00:03:43,849
We don't get network in the house.

88
00:03:45,643 --> 00:03:46,810
Focus, guys!

89
00:03:46,936 --> 00:03:48,604
Come on.

90
00:03:49,438 --> 00:03:51,649
-Bruce, did you see him?
-Where is he?

91
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:52,942
Waiting for target confirmation, sir.

92
00:03:53,025 --> 00:03:54,526
Hello, brother!

93
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:57,154
-Hello. Can you hear me now?
-Play it.

94
00:03:57,613 --> 00:03:58,739
-Hello. 
-Hello?

95
00:03:58,822 --> 00:04:00,240
-I can't hear you. 
-Sajid?

96
00:04:00,324 --> 00:04:01,992
-Do we have anything else?
-Nothing else, sir.

97
00:04:02,076 --> 00:04:03,786
Fuck it! Play this on loop.

98
00:04:04,578 --> 00:04:05,996
I can't hear you, brother!

99
00:04:07,289 --> 00:04:08,916
-Hello, brother? 
-Hello.

100
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:10,709
-I can't hear you. 
 -Hello, Sajid!

101
00:04:10,793 --> 00:04:11,877
The network's bad.

102
00:04:11,961 --> 00:04:13,754
There he is! Zoom in!

103
00:04:14,421 --> 00:04:15,756
-Hello. 
 -I can't hear you.

104
00:04:16,298 --> 00:04:18,676
-Hello, Sajid? 
 -Hello, I can't hear you, brother.

105
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:21,261
-Where are you talking from, hell?
-Target locked, sir.

106
00:04:21,345 --> 00:04:22,179
Srikant.

107
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:24,431
-We got him.
-Yes!

108
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:27,851
Bloody idiot!

109
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:05,514
What is this "Faizan" issue?

110
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:09,643
He was hiding in our country
and we didn't know?

111
00:05:09,727 --> 00:05:12,896
Bin Laden has already brought
us enough embarrassment.

112
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,816
We cannot go through that again.

113
00:05:16,025 --> 00:05:18,235
The embassy has received a
call from the White House.

114
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:21,905
It's no secret that General Ansari
is responsible for this.

115
00:05:22,072 --> 00:05:25,034
Apparently, the ISI is involved as well.

116
00:05:25,993 --> 00:05:27,619
General Khursheed...

117
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:30,706
this is a very serious matter.

118
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:32,541
I agree, sir.

119
00:05:33,292 --> 00:05:38,005
We are checking the travel records
of all our men and agents.

120
00:05:38,088 --> 00:05:40,132
Whoever is responsible for
this will be exposed soon.

121
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:42,342
Hurry up with the investigations.

122
00:05:42,426 --> 00:05:44,386
The Americans have threatened us

123
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:46,722
that they will stop giving us aid.

124
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:49,767
Speak to the Secretary of State.

125
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:52,186
-Yes, sir.
-That's all. Thank you.

126
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:01,361
General Khursheed.

127
00:06:02,237 --> 00:06:03,822
Please wait.

128
00:06:07,159 --> 00:06:09,995
-What's going on, Khursheed?
-I'm sorry, sir.

129
00:06:10,245 --> 00:06:12,998
Ansari's men kept Faizan in hiding.

130
00:06:13,123 --> 00:06:14,708
And what were you doing?

131
00:06:14,792 --> 00:06:17,377
Why didn't you keep
an eye on Ansari?

132
00:06:17,461 --> 00:06:18,962
We did, sir.

133
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:22,883
We trace him every second
he's outside Balochistan.

134
00:06:23,217 --> 00:06:26,011
But on his own turf, we can't do anything.

135
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:29,014
We need to clean up this mess.

136
00:06:29,098 --> 00:06:32,768
What if we need to get rid of Ansari?

137
00:06:32,851 --> 00:06:34,853
That won't be easy.

138
00:06:35,687 --> 00:06:38,148
He fought a war for Pakistan.

139
00:06:38,732 --> 00:06:40,484
He's received
the Nishan-e-Haider award.

140
00:06:40,692 --> 00:06:45,572
He knows the top brass
in the army and the ISI.

141
00:06:46,115 --> 00:06:50,285
Find out about his contacts in the ISI.

142
00:06:52,496 --> 00:06:56,875
We need to tread very carefully.

143
00:07:08,846 --> 00:07:11,473
Wow, Mom! Very cool!

144
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:14,852
You've never dressed up
like this for work.

145
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:17,187
Okay, listen.

146
00:07:17,271 --> 00:07:19,606
I'm going for
an important conference to Lonavala.

147
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:21,733
I will take some time to come back.
Okay?

148
00:07:21,817 --> 00:07:23,902
You're a grown-up.

149
00:07:23,986 --> 00:07:25,863
Look after the house and your brother.

150
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:28,282
Make sure he doesn't play
video games all day.

151
00:07:28,365 --> 00:07:30,367
Those are Math tutorials.

152
00:07:30,492 --> 00:07:33,662
Not everything on the
tablet is a video game!

153
00:07:33,745 --> 00:07:36,039
I have asked Aunt Neelam to cook for you.

154
00:07:36,165 --> 00:07:37,833
Eat whatever she cooks.

155
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:39,793
Do not fuss or waste the food.

156
00:07:39,918 --> 00:07:42,129
And don't mess up the house.
Okay?

157
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:44,756
-If you want something to munch on--
-Mom!

158
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:46,133
Got it.

159
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:50,095
Forgot something else.

160
00:07:50,179 --> 00:07:52,514
-Dhriti, get the door.
-Atharv.

161
00:07:52,890 --> 00:07:54,349
Come on!

162
00:07:59,062 --> 00:07:59,897
Hi!

163
00:08:00,772 --> 00:08:02,065
Atharv, right?

164
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:03,692
I'm Arvind.

165
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:05,777
Mom?

166
00:08:06,278 --> 00:08:07,487
Mom!

167
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,199
There's somebody at the door.

168
00:08:12,201 --> 00:08:13,368
-Hi!
-Hi, Suchi.

169
00:08:13,452 --> 00:08:14,661
-Come in.
-Hey, young lady!

170
00:08:14,745 --> 00:08:16,079
You must be Dhriti, right?

171
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:18,457
Would you like to
have tea or coffee?

172
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:20,125
Filter coffee, if possible.

173
00:08:20,209 --> 00:08:21,210
Sure.

174
00:08:21,293 --> 00:08:22,628
Hello!
Don't you have to go to school?

175
00:08:22,711 --> 00:08:25,547
You're getting late.
Get up, come on! Go!

176
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:28,383
Get up!

177
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:41,980
-Bye.
-Go.

178
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:48,654
Dhriti, lunch box.

179
00:08:49,863 --> 00:08:51,406
-Who is he?
-I told you.

180
00:08:51,490 --> 00:08:52,866
He's my colleague.

181
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:56,954
It looks like you're going
for a picnic, not a conference.

182
00:09:05,963 --> 00:09:09,424
-Don't put too much sugar.
-Shit! You scared me!

183
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:12,761
-How's Rhea?
-She's feeling better.

184
00:09:12,970 --> 00:09:14,304
My mom found out she's ill.

185
00:09:14,388 --> 00:09:15,764
So, she took Rhea with her.

186
00:09:15,847 --> 00:09:17,307
Thank God for grandmas!

187
00:09:17,391 --> 00:09:18,392
-Listen.
-Here you go.

188
00:09:18,475 --> 00:09:19,518
Nikhil is coming from Delhi.

189
00:09:19,601 --> 00:09:20,769
So he'll meet us at the venue.

190
00:09:20,852 --> 00:09:21,979
There's a start-up boot camp.

191
00:09:22,062 --> 00:09:23,355
We'll be meeting our VCs over there.

192
00:09:23,438 --> 00:09:24,523
Boot camp?

193
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:28,568
The techies don't like
the word "conference."

194
00:09:28,652 --> 00:09:31,697
So they call it "boot camp."
Sounds cooler.

195
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:35,867
Nice?

196
00:09:35,951 --> 00:09:37,869
Authentic filter coffee!

197
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:42,749
Sir, the Americans won't budge.

198
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:46,461
They don't care about
Zulfiqar or its threat to us.

199
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:49,423
Sir, please! I want to interrogate Faizan.

200
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:51,508
We neither have time,
nor Moosa and Sajid.

201
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,677
Faizan trained both of them.

202
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:56,972
If anybody knows about their 
 location and plan, it is Faizan.

203
00:09:57,055 --> 00:09:59,224
This is an extraordinary
request, Srikant.

204
00:09:59,308 --> 00:10:01,852
But this is an extraordinary
situation, sir!

205
00:10:02,728 --> 00:10:04,938
You cannot go to
Balochistan officially.

206
00:10:05,022 --> 00:10:07,774
That's alright, sir.
I can go unofficially.

207
00:10:07,858 --> 00:10:09,943
What if you go unofficially...

208
00:10:11,153 --> 00:10:12,904
and something happens to you?

209
00:10:13,739 --> 00:10:15,866
You won't be able to get me out of there.

210
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:18,076
Sir, I've made some mistakes

211
00:10:18,535 --> 00:10:21,163
which killed innocent people.

212
00:10:21,788 --> 00:10:26,543
Sir, this is my only
chance to redeem myself.

213
00:10:26,752 --> 00:10:30,672
My life or any other life 
 it isn't bigger than Zulfiqar.

214
00:10:30,756 --> 00:10:32,424
Sir, my gut feeling says

215
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:34,801
something terrible will happen...

216
00:10:35,594 --> 00:10:38,555
and no one can
imagine its extent.

217
00:10:43,518 --> 00:10:45,228
Qazi is a bastard!

218
00:10:45,312 --> 00:10:46,355
It's shameful

219
00:10:46,438 --> 00:10:50,108
that a coward like him is the
Prime Minister of Pakistan.

220
00:10:51,318 --> 00:10:54,404
I am sure he must have
led the CIA to Faizan.

221
00:10:54,529 --> 00:10:57,949
That son of a bitch
dances to the tune of the whites.

222
00:10:58,033 --> 00:11:01,286
And his butler, Khursheed!
Both the bastards--

223
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:04,039
Sir, I suggest
we commence phase two.

224
00:11:04,206 --> 00:11:06,249
And what about Faizan?

225
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,752
Do you think he'll spill the beans?

226
00:11:08,835 --> 00:11:11,463
Sir, Faizan barely knows
anything about Zulfiqar.

227
00:11:11,838 --> 00:11:13,882
But he could lead them to us.

228
00:11:14,091 --> 00:11:15,801
And you know our Prime Minister.

229
00:11:15,926 --> 00:11:18,970
The moment he finds out,
he'll try to stop us at any cost.

230
00:11:19,054 --> 00:11:21,598
You're right.
Maybe it's time.

231
00:11:22,099 --> 00:11:23,517
Are we ready?

232
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:26,395
We can start phase two in
the next 48 hours.

233
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:27,938
Sameer...

234
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:32,192
we are nearing the end of our mission.

235
00:11:32,901 --> 00:11:36,488
With Allah's grace,
this mission will be a success.

236
00:11:36,655 --> 00:11:37,656
Inshallah!

237
00:11:37,823 --> 00:11:40,409
I'll ensure it succeeds, sir.

238
00:11:44,704 --> 00:11:46,373
The jet belongs to
this guy from Delhi.

239
00:11:46,456 --> 00:11:49,626
He's one of the many businessmen doing
infrastructure work in Afghanistan.

240
00:11:49,751 --> 00:11:52,087
This plane will touchdown
in Kandahar for a while.

241
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:54,631
RAW's asset, Mustafa,
will meet you there.

242
00:11:54,714 --> 00:11:56,633
Balochistan is a two-hour
drive from there.

243
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:58,051
He'll take you there.

244
00:11:58,135 --> 00:12:02,472
Srikant, you know that this
is completely off the record.

245
00:12:02,556 --> 00:12:05,100
If you're caught,
you're on your own.

246
00:12:05,183 --> 00:12:07,185
We cannot extract you.

247
00:12:08,353 --> 00:12:09,813
I know the risks.

248
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,070
Are you sure about this?

249
00:12:18,488 --> 00:12:21,408
There are other ways to
get information from Faizan.

250
00:12:21,533 --> 00:12:23,743
We don't have time for that.

251
00:12:24,536 --> 00:12:26,788
I should've done this
a long time ago, Saloni.

252
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:32,169
Good luck, Srikant.

253
00:12:49,978 --> 00:12:50,896
Hi.

254
00:12:51,188 --> 00:12:52,522
Welcome to the boot camp, sir.

255
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:53,648
