Let's see.

514
00:32:46,590 --> 00:32:47,675
Is everything okay at home?

515
00:32:49,968 --> 00:32:53,097
Yes, everything is fine here.

516
00:32:54,431 --> 00:32:55,724
Don't worry about us.

517
00:32:57,309 --> 00:32:59,978
Your work is important. 
 Focus on it.

518
00:33:01,063 --> 00:33:03,315
Finish it and come back.

519
00:33:04,858 --> 00:33:06,151
Sri...

520
00:33:07,528 --> 00:33:08,779
as soon as possible.

521
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:11,448
They are here.

522
00:33:11,657 --> 00:33:12,866
I need to go now.

523
00:33:12,950 --> 00:33:13,992
Okay?

524
00:33:19,581 --> 00:33:20,708
Thank you.

525
00:34:14,219 --> 00:34:15,304
Hello!

526
00:34:17,306 --> 00:34:18,932
What's happening?

527
00:34:21,185 --> 00:34:22,311
Hello!

528
00:34:27,816 --> 00:34:30,194
-Untie him!
-What's happening?

529
00:34:30,611 --> 00:34:32,404
There's no time to talk.

530
00:34:32,529 --> 00:34:35,032
Get out of here before
someone finds out.

531
00:34:35,616 --> 00:34:36,784
Let's go.

532
00:34:44,958 --> 00:34:46,752
Faizan, let's go!

533
00:35:27,501 --> 00:35:29,169
Thank you for saving my life.

534
00:35:29,253 --> 00:35:31,922
-Are you from the Pakistan Army?
-We are from the ISI.

535
00:35:33,173 --> 00:35:37,511
The Prime Minister himself
planned this operation.

536
00:35:37,636 --> 00:35:39,054
The Prime Minister?

537
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:42,432
Listen to me carefully, Faizan.

538
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:46,812
We had no clue that
you were in Pakistan.

539
00:35:47,062 --> 00:35:49,022
Or that you got caught.

540
00:35:49,147 --> 00:35:52,734
It was very embarrassing
for the Prime Minister.

541
00:35:54,736 --> 00:35:57,656
Pakistan already has
a bad reputation.

542
00:35:57,906 --> 00:35:59,491
And when the world finds out

543
00:35:59,575 --> 00:36:01,451
that we were harboring
a terrorist...

544
00:36:01,869 --> 00:36:04,246
we'll have to face more ridicule.

545
00:36:04,496 --> 00:36:06,874
All the nations in the
world will blacklist us.

546
00:36:07,291 --> 00:36:09,126
I was only following
the sacred word of--

547
00:36:09,209 --> 00:36:10,586
Stop that nonsense!

548
00:36:10,669 --> 00:36:14,423
Save that for your recruits!

549
00:36:14,548 --> 00:36:15,757
Got it?

550
00:36:16,884 --> 00:36:17,968
You don't do it for God.

551
00:36:18,051 --> 00:36:19,803
You do it for the American dollars.

552
00:36:19,887 --> 00:36:21,972
-But I--
-Shut up! Don't you understand?

553
00:36:22,139 --> 00:36:23,891
The Prime Minister got a call

554
00:36:23,974 --> 00:36:27,227
from the Indian Prime Minister
threatening us with war.

555
00:36:27,603 --> 00:36:31,315
Have you sent two of your boys
to India for a mission?

556
00:36:32,232 --> 00:36:34,067
-Mission...
-Zulfiqar.

557
00:36:34,151 --> 00:36:35,694
Mission Zulfiqar.

558
00:36:36,820 --> 00:36:39,156
You have two options, Faizan.

559
00:36:39,281 --> 00:36:41,950
Tell those two guys to
immediately abort the mission

560
00:36:42,034 --> 00:36:43,911
and give us their location.

561
00:36:44,161 --> 00:36:47,873
A car is waiting for you
at the end of this tunnel.

562
00:36:48,165 --> 00:36:50,542
It will take you straight to the airport.

563
00:36:52,002 --> 00:36:56,548
Here's your Saudi passport
and a ticket to Riyadh.

564
00:36:56,632 --> 00:37:00,677
It's a parting gift
from the Prime Minister.

565
00:37:00,761 --> 00:37:02,763
We know that you
funnel all your money

566
00:37:02,846 --> 00:37:06,016
into a secret account in Saudi.

567
00:37:06,850 --> 00:37:11,730
Say goodbye to Pakistan
and lead a peaceful life.

568
00:37:13,607 --> 00:37:17,152
Or, stay six feet under the ground
in Pakistan,

569
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:19,738
buried in an unmarked grave.

570
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:23,992
We don't want Pakistan's name
dragged through the mud

571
00:37:24,576 --> 00:37:26,119
because of you.

572
00:37:29,331 --> 00:37:31,249
What do you want to do?

573
00:37:32,334 --> 00:37:34,086
Can I go to Sudan?

574
00:37:35,295 --> 00:37:37,547
I don't like the
climate in Saudi.

575
00:37:43,845 --> 00:37:45,847
Is the climate in Sudan good?

576
00:37:58,485 --> 00:38:00,153
Who are these people?

577
00:38:00,237 --> 00:38:02,406
They'll be taking you to the airport.

578
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:08,620
Motherfucker!

579
00:38:08,787 --> 00:38:11,373
Bastard! You betrayed me!

580
00:38:11,623 --> 00:38:13,417
I'll screw each one of you!

581
00:38:13,500 --> 00:38:14,751
Bastard!

582
00:38:14,835 --> 00:38:16,420
I hope you got what
you wanted from him.

583
00:38:16,503 --> 00:38:18,588
Got something.
But thank you, Bruce.

584
00:38:18,672 --> 00:38:21,341
-Thank you for your help.
-Anytime, Srikant.

585
00:38:24,678 --> 00:38:27,097
Sir, both Moosa and Sajid
have been trained by Faizan.

586
00:38:27,222 --> 00:38:28,557
A few years ago

587
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:30,308
Lashkar-e-Taiba
got their hands on

588
00:38:30,434 --> 00:38:31,935
a stockpile of nerve gas in POK.

589
00:38:32,019 --> 00:38:33,812
This was later seized by the ISI.

590
00:38:33,895 --> 00:38:37,691
Then, Major Sameer and Ansari 
 planned a secret mission.

591
00:38:37,816 --> 00:38:38,859
Mission Zulfiqar.

592
00:38:38,942 --> 00:38:40,944
Over a few years,
they slowly smuggled it

593
00:38:41,028 --> 00:38:44,656
in small quantities
across the border, into Kashmir.

594
00:38:44,740 --> 00:38:47,826
The nerve gas has been 
 stockpiled in a hideout in Kashmir.

595
00:38:47,909 --> 00:38:49,369
The original plan was that

596
00:38:49,453 --> 00:38:51,371
Moosa and Asif would enter India,

597
00:38:51,455 --> 00:38:54,958
Asif would get all the nerve gas 
 from Kashmir into Delhi,

598
00:38:55,125 --> 00:38:57,294
and Moosa would make 
 a bomb in Delhi.

599
00:38:57,377 --> 00:39:00,422
But after Asif was caught,
Faizan chose Sajid for this task.

600
00:39:00,505 --> 00:39:03,467
Sajid is sharper and
much more dangerous.

601
00:39:03,550 --> 00:39:04,843
If my guess is right

602
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:09,306
then Sajid is currently
getting the nerve gas to Delhi.

603
00:39:09,514 --> 00:39:10,974
Moosa is hiding somewhere.

604
00:39:11,058 --> 00:39:13,143
And these two will meet in Delhi.

605
00:39:13,310 --> 00:39:15,604
Nerve gas attack in Delhi.

606
00:39:17,022 --> 00:39:18,774
-What a disaster!
 -Yes, sir.

607
00:39:18,940 --> 00:39:22,152
This time they didn't go for 
 terrorist attacks like 26/11

608
00:39:22,235 --> 00:39:23,278
or the parliament attack

609
00:39:23,528 --> 00:39:26,656
which were eventually blamed on 
 independent terrorist groups.

610
00:39:26,948 --> 00:39:30,118
Nerve gas attack
means an act of war.

611
00:39:30,702 --> 00:39:33,497
And this is not possible
without the government support.

612
00:39:33,789 --> 00:39:34,831
Which means the Indian government

613
00:39:34,915 --> 00:39:36,833
will have to go to 
 war with Pakistan.

614
00:39:37,209 --> 00:39:39,628
This will give General Ansari
an opportunity

615
00:39:39,753 --> 00:39:41,004
to carry out a coup.

616
00:39:41,088 --> 00:39:43,465
And soon, they'll get control
over the Pakistan government.

617
00:39:43,548 --> 00:39:45,717
Sir, Major Sameer has 
 all the information.

618
00:39:45,801 --> 00:39:48,011
I think we should involve 
 the government of Pakistan.

619
00:39:48,095 --> 00:39:49,429
We have to work together.

620
00:39:49,721 --> 00:39:51,640
If this mission is successful

621
00:39:51,807 --> 00:39:54,601
then this will be disastrous
for both the countries.

622
00:39:55,143 --> 00:39:58,480
-Good job, Srikant.
-Yeah, good job, Srikant.

623
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:02,734
Thank you, sir.

624
00:40:18,708 --> 00:40:19,960
Thanks for waiting, sir.

625
00:40:20,043 --> 00:40:22,337
The honorable PM will join 
 this call in a moment.

626
00:40:22,462 --> 00:40:23,880
Thank you.

627
00:40:26,133 --> 00:40:28,718
-Hello, Mr. Kulkarni. 
-Sir.

628
00:40:29,010 --> 00:40:30,345
I have been briefed thoroughly

629
00:40:30,428 --> 00:40:32,055
about the seriousness 
 of the situation.

630
00:40:32,222 --> 00:40:34,516
I have only one question, Mr. Kulkarni.

631
00:40:34,891 --> 00:40:37,352
And I want a straight and clear answer.

632
00:40:37,978 --> 00:40:40,355
Do they really have 
 a stockpile of nerve gas?

633
00:40:41,731 --> 00:40:42,941
Yes, sir.

634
00:40:43,024 --> 00:40:45,527
Mr. Kulkarni, we cannot afford a war.

635
00:40:45,694 --> 00:40:47,863
But if a nerve gas attack 
 is carried out on us

636
00:40:47,988 --> 00:40:50,282
we'll have to retaliate.

637
00:40:50,365 --> 00:40:54,161
We will have to unwillignly 
 go to war with Pakistan.

638
00:40:54,286 --> 00:40:55,871
I need a solution to this problem.

639
00:40:55,954 --> 00:40:57,664
Let me know what I can do to help.

640
00:40:57,789 --> 00:41:01,501
Sir, you'll need to speak to
the Prime Minister of Pakistan.

641
00:41:02,961 --> 00:41:06,089
You'll need to convince him
to stop his men...

642
00:41:07,090 --> 00:41:09,092
and give us the information...

643
00:41:10,135 --> 00:41:11,928
that we need.

644
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:15,182
How sure are you about 
 this information?

645
00:41:16,766 --> 00:41:19,561
One of our agents is in
Balochistan right now...

646
00:41:20,228 --> 00:41:22,230
and I have full faith in him.
